<br>
I am sure I'll get an item eventually it doesn't really bother me too much either way. I have EER and SS and 61 thru 64 spells (although I don't use post-60 spells much until raid time)<br>
<br>
I still cringe that I replace my Shawl 8 with that horribly bad-stat ODS. But ya know, I have too for mana efficiency.  I also have a jungle fur spider cap. Yup use it a lot (don't try to camp this sucker. Farm small items, sell, and BUY one for 20K or so before you attempt to persuade others to get this). Would rather wear my Circlet of Falinken or maybe a FT1 item but it really pays to use focus.<br>
<br>
The POP split focus effects is a horrible idea and is really a marginal improvement on total damage that seems NOT to be worth it. In fact it almost seems to be a nerf.  <br>
<br>
Bug a mage? Well for one thing, they don't hang around Nexus like those pimp chanters do 24/7. Sure I got guildmates and yes I get a focus 4 bag everytime we raid.  I compromise my stats and put on the ring, bracer and earring. It is just worth it to much not too.<br>
<br>
However self-sufficiency (minus KEI) is everyone's goal yes? Especially when it comes to focus items thats half the fun.<br>
<br>
POP focus are scatter-shot and not very fun. And yes, pretty much impossible to get if you aren't in a guild that is worthy of defeating even Aerin Dar.<br>
<br>
To sum it up: <br>
<br>
1.) Original poster was correct. Ain't much use in obtaining your level 61-65 spells as long as you have SS and EER/GSS I would have to agree.<br>
<br>
2.) Sony completely shifted gears on focus effects. a) they made it NEAR impossible for the more casual player whereas before you could get focus rather easily. b) they split the effects and made it even more schizophrenic  c) mages have it all covered so whats the point really<br>
<br>
3.) CT is empty anymore. Even your friggin friends are going to say &quot;well tough shit, there is so much that needs to be done in POP (quests, exp, etc.) that you are SOL we just don't have time for that&quot;. That is a fact even for people like Rombus and Frozboz would probably have a hard time dragging guildies back to CT for a Spider Fur Cap.<br>
<br>
4) POP spells (except Ice flame) are generally a boring, more of the same. And they are NOT worth using if you don't have the appropriate focus effect as the original poster stated. Thats a fact no matter how you slice it. The negative 50 modifier? Big whoop-de-doo, my 60 or less spells do just as as well on the whole with focus.<br>
<br>
5) The mage focus bag kind of makes it all a moot point deosn't it???. I mean what incentive do I have to obtain a POP specialized focus item (that perhaps sacrifices my stats in some way) when I can just beg a mage and viola, I am uber focus wizard!!  It all seems so pointless anyway.  If I am armed with a mage focus 4 bag, I am just as well off as someone who has labored and earned his own focus effect items.<br>
<br>
No POP is not for the casual gamer. The sad thing is that even the hardcore gamer has found this expansion to be just another labor....and a GAME should be fun. Give us more fun spells, etc.<br>
<br>
POP is turning out to be not very fun after all, even when I have access to more and more zones. Once again it all feels like pressured work. Miss a raid? Too bad buddy, you can't advance with your buddies cause you had to work and earn a living. key this, flag that. BAH!<br>
<br>
Even the POP AAXP abilities sucks pretty bad. Don't get me started on that.....<br>
<br>
Daneric<br>
Arcanist<br>
Crsuaders of Plilo<br>
<br>
EDIT: I truly LIKE the POP design but I think it needs tweaking a bit. If my guild kills uber mob A, we shouldn't have to kill him again just to get TWO friggin people the flag...should be some sort of /guild default setting.....<br>
<br>
Also the total experience nerf (in effect a nerf) of the old worlds was totally unexpected and unjustified....anyway you slice it you just neutered 90% of the game..all due to shortsighted &quot;vision&quot; and truly baffling design choices. Mostly I think its due to poor programming that doesn't fit well with older programming...<br>
<br>
Not enough &quot;fun&quot; in the game left.  I could get 200 AA and it don't mean squat. Not much better than 100 AA. C'mon THINK OUTSIDE THE BOX!! Let me earn a decent SLOW AA ability for my 200 AA. let me get some cool worthwhile AA ability nuke for my time spent.<br>
<br>
OHHHHHHH!!!!!!!!!!!! Another stupid straight-laced DD NUKE!! Hrmm, I'm IMPRESSED SONY!!! WOOOO!! 3.89 ratio!!!<br>
<br>
WOOOOOOTTTT!!!! With eggnog focus 6.1 I can milk that maybe to 4.56!!!!!! OHHH look at THIS one! A pack of flaming gay swords that DOES 1-2 PERCENT DAMAGE to the mob I'm soloing in HOH!!!! WOW that will SURELY SAVE ME a hit or 2 of manastoning....and I only spent 6 AA!<br>
<br>
OMG I just can't wait to hit 300 AAA so my raw magic resist will be 200 and fucking 20 instead of just 200!!!<br>
<br>
Yeah right...<br>
<br>
Seriously, hitting 100 or 200 or 300 AA (or even just 75 or whatever, you get what I am saying) should unlock other classes abilities in some way...or give us a really worthwhile ability.....mana-free nuke on the order of a 10 second, 800 hp nuke that can be cast every 6 minutes or so....I mean I ain't talking about unbalancing-type things, I am just saying MAKE IT FUN AGAIN!!!<br>
<br>
make it worthwhile and not just another grind...<br>
<br>
